result.execSummary:
The defendant Jay A. Graham was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Case called @ 2:45 p.m. Defendant Jay A. Graham in court appears telephonically.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. The defendant waives his right to be personally present in the courtroom.   Defendant advised of right to counsel and expertise.  Voluntary waiver of counsel accepted by Court.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Plea: Ct 1 - NC.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Ct 2 - DRI. No statement by DE. Court orders: Costs w/ 60 DTP or PP. The court does not order the DNA sample to be submitted. Appeal rights mailed to DE.

Pre-trial conference at 08-12-2015 10:30 am.
Status conference at 09-01-2015 01:15 pm.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.

Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel. Defendant will not be represented by SPD if released from custoday. ADA Anderson requesting $1000 Sig Bond. No objection by Atty Szilagyi.  NGP entered. The court will allow the defendant to appear telephonically at any future hearings.  STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for August 12, 2015 at 10:30 am.  Status conference scheduled for September 1, 2015 at 01:15 pm.
